term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), a fascinating blow-by-blow of the house=E2=80=
=99s big auction earlier this week. On the one hand, the $267 million in ag=
gregate hammer sales were up 30 percent over the previous year. On the othe=
r, the whole affair was colored by a decidedly melancholy mood, with only a=
 single bidder or two on many lots. And yet, this fate was decidedly prefer=
able to that of Christie=E2=80=99s, whose website fell victim to a cyberatt=
ack during the most important bidding week on the calendar. If you want a m=
ore poignant view about where the market is headed, I=E2=80=99d direct your=
